    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/future-reserves-2020-consultation"/>
    <title>Future Reserves 2020 Consultation</title>
    <category>Consultation</category>
    <summary>On 5 July 2012, the Secretary of State for Defence responded to the Review of the United Kingdom’s Reserve Forces published on 18 July 2011. Given the scale of change required, he requested the Ministry of Defence carry out a formal public consultation on how to achieve our vision for the Future Reserve Forces (FR20).</summary>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The United Kingdom’s Reserve Forces are a vital component of our Armed Forces; contributing to the public good we call Defence. They have made, and continue to make, a significant contribution to the Nation’s defence and security. But the security challenges the UK will face in future are different from those of the past, and for which our Reserve Forces are currently structured. Over the next decade, as Defence transforms to meet future and uncertain challenges, so the importance of our Reserve Forces will increase, and the way we organise and use them will change.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The consultation exercise will consider what changes are required to the Reserve Forces in order to generate and sustain the numbers and capabilities we need from them to meet our defence requirements. Specifically, we will look to define the right offer to attract and retain the individuals we need to serve in the reserves; the right relationship with the civilian employers of reservists; and the right support for reservists and their families across our communities.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Consultation (Green) Paper sets out our thinking and direction of travel on Future Reserve. The key areas on which the paper focuses include:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;How we will use Reserve Forces in the future&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The offer for employers&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;The offer for reservists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;Responses to the Green Paper can be provided online from early November. We encourage you to engage and provide feedback.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A White Paper in 2013 will detail the policy changes for Reserves and show how changes will be implemented to establish a new force structure such that we create the strategic conditions for success. Responses received during the consultation exercise will be used to inform the White Paper.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A case study of Iain Ballantyne, intelligence analyst with the RAF Reserves, can be found below. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any enquiries or questions about the consultation process should be directed to &lt;a href="mailto:DCDSPers-RFC-FR20Consultation@mod.uk" title="Email enquiries or questions"&gt;DCDSPers-RFC-FR20Consultation@mod.uk&lt;/a&gt;. Please note this email address should not be used to send responses to the Green Paper - Please respond via the online survey at the Respond Online link below. For enquires, you can also write to the address below.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
